                  <interp inst="t18221023-80-crimeloc442" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18221023-80-off439 t18221023-80-crimeloc442"></join>. The prisoner was one week in our service, and left on the 1st of October. I asked her to allow me to look into her box - she said not without a constable. I said I did not wish a piece of work, and if she was honest she would let me. She turned round and struck me in the face, and tore my gown. I gave her in charge for an assault - and next night she came for her boxes. I sent for Summers, who found these things in her box.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Does not your sister live in the house - A. Yes.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18221023-80-person887">
                  JOHN 
                  SUMMERS
